Paper: hep-th/9510193

Date: 1995-10-26

Title: Positronium as an example of algebraic composite calculations

Authors: Bertfried Fauser (Bertfried.Fauser@uni-tuebingen.de) and Harald Stumpf

Comments: LateX (article.sty, orig. was for Kapproc.sty) 19 pages no figures,

to appear in proceedings of the `International Conference on the Theory ofthe Electron' 1995, Cuautitlan Mexico, Z. Oziewic, J. Keller (eds.)Journal-ref: Adv.Appl.Clifford Algebras 7 (1997) S399-S418

The functional quantum field theory, developed by Stumpf, provides thepossibility to derive the quantum dynamics of a positronium gas from Coulombinteracting electrons and positrons. By this example, the method will bebrought in a Clifford algebraic light, through identifying the functional spacewith an infinite dimensional Euclidean Clifford algebra.